      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SEASIDE BOY (10) is a progressive colt who has easily won all three starts this time in, leading to cruise home by 11m here last week. A second row draw presents as a new challenge but he won the only time he attempted this shorter distance and he looks bound for better things. HOORAH PHILTRA (5) has been very good in two outings at this circuit and distance since joining Ashleigh Herbertson, racing parked but proving too good by 2.8m then coming from this barrier to miss by a nose last time. Could atone. OZZIE CORKA (3) draws well and is heading the right way, putting the writing on the wall with a close second here last week. HAPPILY (8) scored for the second time in four starts so far this campaign when coming from this barrier to salute by 7m at Horsham. That took his record at this distance to two wins and placing from three attempts and he has upside. KEAYANG PAYTON (4) has been consistent in three Victorian outings since a win in SA. Include.",
